      "type": "concept",
      "title": "Details",
      "content": "Include an HTML file:\nw3.includeHTML()\nThe HTML\nSave the HTML you want to include in an .html file:\ncontent.html\n<a href=\"https://www..com/html/\">HTML</a><br>\n<a \n href=\"https://www..com/css/\">CSS</a><br>\n<a \n href=\"https://www..com/bootstrap/\">Bootstrap</a><br>\n<a \n href=\"https://www..com/js/\">JavaScript</a><br>\n<a \n href=\"https://www..com/sql/\">SQL</a><br>\n<a \n href=\"https://www..com/php/\">PHP</a><br>\n<a \n href=\"https://www..com/w3css/\">W3.CSS</a><br>\nInclude the HTML\nIncluding HTML is done by using a\nw3-include-html\nattribute:\nExample\n<div\nw3-include-html\n=\"content.html\"></div>\nAdd the JavaScript\nHTML includes are done by JavaScript.\nMake sure your page has\nw3.js\nloaded and call\nw3.includeHTML()\n:\nExample\n<script>\nw3.includeHTML();\n</script>\nFull Example\nExample\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<script src=\"/lib/w3.js\"></script>\n<body>\n<div w3-include-html=\"content.html\"></div>\n<script>\nw3.includeHTML();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>\n\nWith CSS \u00bb\nInclude Many HTML Snippets\nYou can include any number of HTML snippets:\nExample\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<script src=\"/lib/w3.js\"></script>\n<body>\n<div w3-include-HTML=\"h1.html\"></div>\n<div w3-include-HTML=\"content.html\"></div>\n<script>\nw3.includeHTML();\n</script>\n</body>\n<html>\n\nWith CSS \u00bb\nAdding a Callback Function\nWhen you include HTML snippets in a web page, you must secure that other \nfunctions that depends on the included HTML do not execute before the HTML is \nproperly included.\nThe easiest way to \"hold back\" code is to place it in a callback function.\nA callback function can be added as an argument to w3.includeHTML():\nExample\n<script>\nw3.includeHTML(\nmyCallback\n);\nfunction myCallback() {\n// code that has to wait goes here\n}\n</script>\nYou will find a callback example in the\n\n\u2605\n+1",
